         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Renal Dialysis Services within the East Midlands Renal Network</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>DN319576</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="85111900"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Prior information notice without a call for competition. This is a call for preliminary market consultations to inform a potential procurement exercise.</P>
               <P>This notice is being released to the market to allow interested parties - which could include Independent Providers, NHS Providers, Consortia and other suitably qualified organisations the opportunity to register an interest.</P>
               <P>University Hospitals of Leicester (UHL) is seeking expressions of interest from suitably qualified organisations who are able to provide innovative solutions - not necessarily based on current pathways or facilities footprint.</P>
               <P>Through the Provision of a Managed Service for the Transformation of Renal Dialysis Services within the East Midlands Renal network. UHL are seeking to achieve clinically and financially sustainable dialysis units across the Network with the capacity to meet the population’s renal replacement health needs with continued provision of a high-quality hemodialysis close to patients’ homes.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKF"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The possible service specification could require various infrastructural developments such as new satellite dialysis units and refurbishment and/or re-equipment and adaptation of other existing dialysis units to facilitate and enable delivery of the clinical model and pathways and include; the provision and maintenance of facilities and equipment, the provision of HD consumables and clinical staff which could include in centre haemodialysis, taking place in main or satellite dialysis units, peritoneal dialysis and home hemodialysis.</P>
                  <P>All organisations registering an interest (see section V1.3 for instructions) will be invited to pre-procurement engagement meetings with UHL representatives to discuss the thinking going forward and the opportunities that are seen for the Trust. Meetings will be individually scheduled following the closing date of the PIN.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-01-30</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <NO_CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Please note that expressions of interest must be made via the Due North e-tendering portal. Please log on to:</P>
               <P>— http://www.supplying2nhs.org/</P>
               <P>— scroll down to Supplier Guide How to Do Business (on the right-hand side of the screen).</P>
               <P>Please then follow the registration instructions (if you are not registered already).</P>
               <P>Once registered the Expressions of Interest section can be found within project reference: DN319576.</P>
               <P>Expressions of interest must be made no later than 17:00 on Thursday, 1.3.2018.</P>
               <P>Please note that this exercise is not part of a selection process and is no indication of a commitment to participate in the Transformation of Renal Dialysis Services procurement process nor does it infer any special status on those Providers who do submit an interest. This notice does not commit University Hospitals Leicester to undertake the procurement of the Transformation of Renal Dialysis Services and University Hospitals Leicester has the right to withdraw the notice.</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-01-26</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
      </F01_2014>
